						               													<description>The board game for the German TV show&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We are looking for the best innovators and investors - because projects not only have to be assessed, they also have to be sold well! Alternately, the players take on the roles of the candidates and the lions. If it is your turn as a candidate, introduce one of the 50 included projects and try to convince the lions of your business idea. He also has a secret mission to perform that can earn him a bonus. Special events make every deal unique. As soon as the project has been presented, it is the lions' turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As in the show, there is now a lot of discussion and haggling, because everyone wants to make the best deals. While the lions want to win as many shares as possible, the candidate is careful to the contrary. Once all the lions have submitted their offers or have spoken the magic words &amp;quot;I'm out!&amp;quot;, The candidate has to choose one of the offers or reject all. Now it becomes clear whether the project has been successful. so the shares he gets will decide the winning and the losing. If the candidate has given too many shares, he can also make losses! As soon as each player has the role of the candidate, the game ends and the player with the most money wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher (translated)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
